# Guidance

Write your architectural rules, coding conventions, and workflow constraints here. Each guideline should be a titled section that the assistant must follow when formulating plans and implementing changes.

This file is gitignored because it contains user-specific project guidance. To get started:

```bash
cp GUIDANCE.md.example GUIDANCE.md
```

Then replace the example guidelines below with your own.

---

### Guidance: Preserve existing functionality.

Do not remove or alter existing behavior unless explicitly told to do so. New changes should be additive where possible.

### Guidance: Follow established architecture.

Honor the patterns and conventions already established in the codebase. Do not introduce novel approaches when existing patterns serve the purpose.
